  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> pizza base mix</strong> (yes this works for pasta too!) to a large bowl and make a well in the middle of it</p><p>Pour 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>warm water</strong> into the well with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix to form a dough</p><p>Tip:<strong> </strong>Add a very small amount more warm water if your dough is looking a little dry and give it a good mix. If your dough is too wet, add a little plain flour. Keep adding more water or flour until your dough is a kneadable texture</p><p>Tip the<strong> dough</strong> onto a <strong>clean, dry work surface</strong> and knead for 8-10 min, or until it's smooth and soft, but not sticky or dry</p><p>Once done, wrap your dough in <strong>cling film </strong>and set aside to rest for 30 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1611673797108-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1611673797108-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1611673797108-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1611673797108-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1611673797108-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 30 min, unwrap your dough and add it to a <strong>very clean, dry work surface</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't use any flour as this will make rolling your pici very tricky!</p><p>Roll the dough into a rough rectangle, approx. 2 cm thick using a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Lightly dust a chopping board with <strong>plain flour</strong> (but not your work surface!) and set it next to your clean work surface</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1611673876823-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1611673876823-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1611673876823-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1611673876823-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1611673876823-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To make your first pici nest, cut a thin strip from your rectangle of dough and add it to your dry work surface</p><p>Put both of your hands in the middle of the <strong>dough strip</strong> and roll them back and forward, moving your hands outwards as you go</p><p>Keep rolling until you are left with a long, thick worm-like spaghetti shape, approx. 5mm thick</p><p>Once rolled, add it to the floured chopping board, then continue to cut and roll the dough strips until you have 10 pieces on the chopping board – these are your<strong> pici</strong></p><p>Tip: Try to aim for a consistent shape so that they cook evenly!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1611673895339-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1611673895339-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1611673895339-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1611673895339-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1611673895339-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle another light dusting of<strong> flour</strong> over the 10 pici pieces (make sure they're nicely coated so that they don't stick together), then pick the pici up and wrap them neatly around your hand to form a nest</p><p>Set the<strong> pici nest</strong> aside on a separate baking tray or chopping board, then repeat this process for the rest of your pici nests until you've used up all of your dough</p><p>Tip: Cooking this for someone special? Get them involved in the fun too!</p><p>Once done, set the pici nests aside to dry out slightly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1611673910886-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1611673910886-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1611673910886-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1611673910886-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1611673910886-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a medium pot over a medium heat and add the <strong>pine nuts</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until lightly toasted, shaking the pot every so often for even colouring</p><p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong> lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add <strong>most</strong> of the<strong> toasted pine nuts</strong> (save some for garnish!) to a <strong>food processor </strong>and reserve the pot</p><p>Add the<strong> basil</strong> with the<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>half</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> of the <strong>garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of <strong>1</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon quarter<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> homemade pesto</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1611673933574-x200.jpg",
