          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to the reserved pot and cover them with<strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite, then drain</p><p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Combine the<strong> chopped shallot</strong> with the <strong>juice </strong>of <strong>2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>lemon quarters</strong>, a drizzle of<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1611673977095-x200.jpg",
